          <div class="faq-answer">theStacc requires no SEO knowledge, no content writing, and no time investment. Sign up, connect your site, and content publishes automatically. Rankings build over time. The Local SEO module starts at $49/month.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How much should a small business spend on local SEO per month?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">$50–200/month covers what most single-location businesses need. theStacc handles content ($49–126/mo), BrightLocal handles tracking ($39/mo), Moz Local handles citations ($20/mo). Don't exceed $200/month until you have consistent content and an optimized GBP profile.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Can I do local SEO for free?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Claim Google Business Profile for free and manually submit to directories. Expect 15+ hours monthly to post GBP updates, write blog content, check citations, and respond to reviews. Paid tools automate these tasks for $50–150/month. For most business owners, that trade is worth it.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">Do small businesses really need blog content for local SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Yes. Businesses publishing blog content rank for 3–5× more keywords than those with only a homepage and service pages. Blog posts targeting local terms build topical authority that GBP alone can't create. Content compounds — articles keep generating traffic for years after they publish.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What's the difference between local SEO and regular SEO?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">Regular SEO focuses on organic website rankings. Local SEO focuses on Google Maps, the local 3-pack, directory listings, citations, and GBP optimization. A business can rank #1 organically but remain completely invisible in Maps.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How long does local SEO take to show results?<span class="faq-icon"><svg><use href="#i-plus"/></svg></span></button>
          <div class="faq-answer">GBP optimizations improve local pack rankings within 2–4 weeks. Blog content typically ranks within 60–90 days. Citation cleanup takes 4–8 weeks to propagate. Most businesses see measurable improvements within 3–6 months of consistent effort.</div>
